subSections.title: Glyph origin
subSections.text:
Unorthodox variant {{Han simp|榲|f=𥁕|t=昷|nocap=y}} that can be found in various historical dictionaries. <!-- Refer http://dict.variants.moe.edu.tw/variants/rbt/word_attribute.rbt?quote_code=QzA1MzA4LTAwMQ -->

Eventually adopted as an official form by the People's Republic of China in 1965 based on the {{w|Xin Zixing}} ({{w2|zh|新字形}}) standardized form of characters.

subSections.title: Usage notes
subSections.text: This character is the preferred form used in Hong Kong, where traditional Chinese is used. <!-- Refer HKSCS 2016 (Page 35) -->
